modules.description: Provides AES, RSA, and elliptic curve operations with built-in support for secure random number generation and protection against timing attacks. Works with byte sequences, keys, and cryptographic contexts for encryption, decryption, and signing. Used to implement secure communication protocols and data integrity checks in networked applications.

Initializes a random number generator with optional sleep duration between entropy collection cycles, ensuring it becomes the default source. Works with `Mirage_crypto_rng.generator` types to manage entropy feeding. Used to set up secure, periodically refreshed random number generation in network or system contexts.
